# Upstream Protection Rule

This repository is a fork of `spring-petclinic/spring-petclinic-rest`. The upstream repo is NOT ours.

## You MUST follow these rules for every git operation:

### Pushing Code
- ONLY push to the `ChrisatCursor` fork. The remote origin after cloning this repo should be `github.com/ChrisatCursor/spring-petclinic-rest`.
- NEVER push to `spring-petclinic/spring-petclinic-rest`.
- Before pushing, run `git remote -v` and confirm the push target is `ChrisatCursor`.

### Pull Requests
- ONLY open pull requests targeting the `ChrisatCursor` fork.
- The base repository for any PR MUST be `ChrisatCursor/spring-petclinic-rest`.
- NEVER open a pull request against `spring-petclinic/spring-petclinic-rest`.
- When using `gh pr create`, always specify: `gh pr create --repo ChrisatCursor/spring-petclinic-rest`

### Branching
- Do not modify the main/master branch directly. Create a feature or migration branch and PR it into the fork's main/master.

### Verification Before Any Push or PR
Run this check and confirm BEFORE every push or PR creation:
```
git remote -v
# ✅ origin should show: github.com/ChrisatCursor/spring-petclinic-rest
# ❌ If origin shows spring-petclinic/, STOP and fix it
```

### Why This Matters
This is a fork of someone else's open-source project used as a starting point for migration demos. We have no business pushing code or PRs to the original project. All work stays in our fork.
